@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Ixo" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, the game requires a 68020(+)
Amiga with Workbench 2.0 or higher and it must have at least 8
colours.

                             How to play?

  The game is played on an 8 by 8 spaces game board in which some
coloured bars have been randomly placed. The next bar that is to be
placed is displayed at the right of the game board. To play, click
on one of the small square dots, or a bar that has a diferent shape
than the one to be placed.

  When you have placed 8 horizontal bars in a row or 8 vertical
bars in a column, those bars are removed (including crossing bars,
if there are any) and you will get points; If the 8 bars are of the
same colour and do not cross any other bars, you get 100 points. If
these same bars cross one or more bars, you get 10 points. If the 8
bars are of different colours, whether they cross other bars or
not, you get 1 point.

  However, from time to time along the game, some bars that have
previously been removed, can reappear at the position they were at
initially...

  In addition, after a while, cross shaped blocks can appear on
empty spaces. These blocks cannot be removed, and one of them may
disappear... and reappear somewhere else on the board. There cannot
be more than 7 blocks at any time on the board and none of them can
be in line, horizontally or vertically, with another block...

  The game has a 'ClickoMeter', what's that? It is a display which
shows how many times you can click on the game board to place
bars... and get the highest possible score. The ClickoMeter is
represented by a 16 branch star, which appears at the right of the
game board. As the game progresses, the number of branches
decrease, and when there are no remaining branches, the game
ends...

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

